#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:4
msgid ""
"PowerNV (as Non-Virtualized) is the \"baremetal\" platform using the OPAL "
"firmware. It runs Linux on IBM and OpenPOWER systems and it can be used as "
"an hypervisor OS, running KVM guests, or simply as a host OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:9
msgid ""
"The PowerNV QEMU machine tries to emulate a PowerNV system at the level of "
"the skiboot firmware, which loads the OS and provides some runtime services. "
"Power Systems have a lower firmware (HostBoot) that does low level system "
"initialization, like DRAM training. This is beyond the scope of what QEMU "
"addresses today."
msgstr ""

